@node "Premiere_Encrypting" "Premiere-Encrypting"
How does premiere-encrypting work? The German Pay-TV Premiere uses the
Syster or Nagravision encrypting. The lines of each frame are stored in
in a buffer. Then the lines are read again from the buffer in random order.
The result is a crippled picture, but you can see big structures and
vertical lines. Because of the wrong line order, the Pal-decoder does not
work and the colors of most lines will be lost.

The Premiere-Mode is activated by the <Sky/Premiere> cycle gadget. The
slider <colors> is used to select the number of lines that will be
displayed in color, the rest bill appear black and white.
5 - 10 % should be a good value.

@endnode

@node "Sky_Encrypting" "Sky-Encrypting"
How does Sky-encrypting work? Sky uses a line-cut-and rotating-system.
Each line will be broken into two parts at a random cut point. Then these
two parts will swap their positions. The result is a completely crippled
picture. There are no visible structures left. You can only see, if the
picture is dark or light and does it contain big horizontal structures.

The Sky-Mode is activated by the <Sky/Premiere> cycle gadget. The
slider <colors> is used to select the number of lines that will be
displayed in color, the rest bill appear black and white.
5 - 10 % should be a good value.

@endnode

@node "DataRate" "about DataRate"
The datarate of the encrypted video is growing, so be carefull! You can
try a lower JPEG quality or you can blur the encrypted video.
@endnode

